    1.3  “Personal Device” means consumer-grade hardware that (a) is owned
         or leased exclusively at the user’s personal expense, (b) is used
         predominantly for non-commercial, private purposes, and (c) is not
         reimbursed, subsidised, or provided by any business, employer,
         client, school, or other organisation.

    1.4  “Commercial Use” means any use, reproduction, modification,
         distribution, public performance, public display, or making
         available of the Software or a Derivative Work, in whole or in
         part, (a) by, for, on behalf of, or for the benefit of any
         organisation or third party; (b) in connection with any activity
         that is monetised or intended to be monetised (including donations,
         sponsorships, advertising, paid support, or subscription access);
         or (c) that facilitates, enables, or powers any product, service,
         or workflow—internal or external—that is supplied to, or accessed
         by, persons other than You.

    1.5  “Derivative Work” means any work, in any medium, that is based on,
         incorporates, translates, adapts, abridges, condenses, or otherwise
         modifies or transforms all or any portion of the Software.

    1.6  “Distribute” or “Distribution” means to sell, license, sublicense,
         lease, lend, rent, gift, publish, transmit, broadcast, host, make
         available, provide access to, or otherwise convey or expose,
         directly or indirectly, the Software, its functionality, or any
         Derivative Work to any third party, whether by physical transfer,
