9.  COMPLIANCE VERIFICATION (AUDIT)
    Upon fourteen (14) days’ written notice, and no more than once in any
    twelve-month period unless material non-compliance is found, the Owner
    or its independent auditor may audit Your records and systems solely to
    verify compliance with this License.  The audit shall occur during
    normal business hours and be subject to reasonable confidentiality
    obligations.  If an audit reveals material non-compliance (defined as
    any violation affecting more than five per cent of installations or
    usage), You shall promptly (a) obtain the requisite CDL(s) retroactive
    to the date the non-compliance began, (b) pay the reasonable costs of
    the audit, and (c) implement corrective measures.

10. TELEMETRY, PRIVACY & DATA PROTECTION
    10.1 Collection.  The Software may automatically collect and transmit
         Telemetry Data—such as unique installation IDs, operating-system
         details, feature-usage frequency, performance metrics, and error
         logs—to the Owner.

    10.2 Purpose.  Telemetry Data is processed for the legitimate interests
         of (a) improving the Software, (b) providing support, and (c)
         verifying compliance with this License.  Telemetry Data is not sold
         to third parties.

    10.3 Personal Data.  Where Telemetry Data constitutes personal data
         under the UK GDPR, EU GDPR, CCPA, or similar laws, the Owner shall
         process such data in accordance with those laws under the lawful
         basis of legitimate interests.  You are responsible for ensuring
         that Your use of the Software, including any processing of personal
         data, complies with all applicable laws.

    10.4 Opt-Out.  If the Software provides an in-product setting to disable
         telemetry, You may exercise that option.  If no such setting is
         provided, Your only means of opting out is to cease using the
         Software.

    10.5 Security & Retention.  The Owner shall implement commercially
         reasonable technical and organisational measures to protect
         Telemetry Data and shall retain Telemetry Data only as long as
         necessary for the purposes stated above or as required by law.

